Definition: a violent kind of alcoholic fermentation at a temperature high enough to carry the yeast cells to the top of the fermenting liquid
Example: used in the production of ale; top fermentation uses a yeast that ferments at higher temperatures than that used for bottom fermentation
Synonyms: zymosis, a, violent, kind, of, alcoholic, fermentation, at, temperature, high, enough, to, carry, the, yeast, cells, top, fermenting, liquid, used, in, production, ale, uses, that, ferments, higher, temperatures, than, for, bottom
Category: noun.process
